cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.SE, cs.PL, cs.LO 

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper presents a decentralized algorithm for distributed, parallel simulations of bigraphical reactive systems. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper discusses algorithms for computing bigraphical embeddings. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is a possible category as the paper presents a new approach to dealing with large bigraphs and parallelizing reactions in bigraphical reactive systems. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is a possible category as the paper discusses the implementation of a decentralized algorithm for bigraphical reactive systems. 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is a possible category as bigraphs and bigraphical reactive systems are based on mathematical logic.
